text_Andesite: Andesite appears to be lighter in color in general. The spots seem to be more defined and lighter. It also looks like some andesite may have holes.
text_Gabbro: Gabbro looks rougher in general and appear to be a more even coloring. Though the actual color of the rocks seems to vary a little bit. The white spots are more plentiful and small/less defined.
Much less defined spotting and can be different shades of gray/brownish.
text_Diorite: Diorite seems to been much more contrasted. It also looks like it's mainly different shades of black and white.

text_Peridotite: Peridotite seems to have a mostly gray surface with green spots.
text_Pegmatite: Pegmatite seems to have cylinders throughout the rock.
